column2: Migrated from EPA STORET Legacy Database- originally reported by Wisconsin DNR
First time monitored- mostly cloudy- calm winds- loons with 2 chicks
Mostly sunny- light wind- loons without chicks
Mostly cloudy- overcast- light SE wind
Weather- partly cloudy- moderate NW wind- light chop on water.
Overcast- threatening rain- light NE breeze.  Assumed sample time was noon.
Clear skies- light breeze from south
Overcast- moderate N winds- light chop on water- brief heavy rain last night
Hazy overcast- light winds e- light ripple
Hazy overcast- calm wind- mirror like lake
Weather is sunny- wind from the north- waves about 6 inches.  This will be the last reading for the year.
Mostly sunny-wind from se-waves less than 6".
Weather sunny- slight ripple- baby loon getting big.
Partly cloudy-wind from west- 6" chop on water.
Overcast + light winds.  Very heavy rain yesterday.
Secchi reading of 11' is an average of 5 readings.  Never saw water this clear!  last few days have been very calm + no rain was very light.  Today is very clear and calm.
7-10" of rain from 9/12 to 9/15.  Secchi disc depth last week was 11'.  Weather - clear and windy.  One foot waves.
Weather clear - about 4" chop on water - last report for 1994.
Clear skies - light wind from north about 4-6" chop on water.  First sample for '95.
Clear to mostly sunny.  South wind about 6" waves.
Clear- hot- light breeze.  Hot + calm for over a week.
Partly cloudy-south-southwest wind.  One foot chop on water- very windy yesterday.  Loon still on nest.
Mostly sunny- light breeze from north 1-12" waves.  Rain last night.  Loon still on nest.
Heavy rain 7/14-15/95.  Partly cloudy light north wind.  2" waves- loon still on nest!  Lake level: Rising
Mostly sunny- light breeze from west- 2-3" waves.  Baby loon hatched this week!  it's about time!
Clear sky-light wind- 1-2" waves.  Baby loon doing fine!
Partly cloudy- 3" waves from se.  Baby loon doing well.  Lots for rain past week.
Partly cloudy- 4" waves from se.  Baby loon about the size of adult mallards.
Clear skies- very light breeze from west.
Clear light breeze from west.  Frost last three nights.
Clear-strong wind from northwest.  Lots of rain this a.m.  Lot of green run-off.
Absolutely beautiful day-no clouds and dead calm.
Lots of pollen + windy last few days.
Partly/mostly cloudy + calm. no baby loon this year.
Perfectly clear. breeze from se. lots of rain past week! very windy yesterday.
Mostly sunny.  Dead calm.  Unseasonably cold last week- lows in low 40s- highs in 60s.
Partly cloudy.  Light wind from south.  Lots and lots and lots of rain 8/7/96.
Absolutely perfect day!  clear skies- light breeze from the west.
Clear skies-gusty wind from southwest. almost strong enough for whitecaps.
Mostly sunny- light breeze from southwest. no rain for past week.
Sunny-wind from east. nice today- 70 degrees. cold past week (high 50's) .
Water almost clear/blue. cold!! beautiful day. clear + windy. whitecaps from south- 72 degrees F. almost peak fall color.
Clear skies- wind from south. last sample for 1996!
Lots of pollen.  First sample of 1997.
1 foot waves from the south.  Windy.  Very little loon activity all spring.  No chicks yet.
Partly cloudy.  North wind at 8-10 mph.  Waves and lots of rain this past week.
Overcast with a southerly wind  8 inch waves.  First sighting of 2 loon chicks with the adults.
Mostly sunny and calm.  Baby loons are twice the size of last week.
Sunny and calm.  Loons are doing fine.
Sunny and warm.  Light NW winds.  Loons are okay.
Overcast.  South wind.  5 adult loons on lake last night.
Clear sky- light winds from the south
Mostly cloudy- light winds out of northwest.
Clear and calm- perfect for a test- young loons are independent of parents but not yet flying
Partly cloudy and windy from the north- rain on 9/19/97- saw young loons with adults previously they were out by themselves
Clear and calm- lake level down 6 inches over the last 3 weeks.
Lots of cotton and pollen/tent caterpillars
S wind- 8 to 10 inch waves.  Loon on nest.
Loon off nest- have not seen chicks.
Windy- 12-18 inch waves.  No loon chicks yet.
8 inch waves from NW- hot 90 degrees.
Clear and cold last night- 45 degrees.
First sample of year.  Partly cloudy.  Light wind from west.  Lots of pollen.
Partly cloudy- wind from NE.  Cold last week.
Partly cloudy - light wind from south.  Huge population of forest tent caterpillars.
Mostly sunny now with intermittent showers - satellite monitor today.
Notable algae bloom on 6/25 that was significantly less on 6/26.
Partly cloudy- wind SW- almost calm- 7 inches of rain from 7/7 to 7/9.
North wind- 5" waves - water level almost back to normal.
No loon chicks this year again.
Partly cloudy- brisk north wind- 8" waves.
Beautiful!  last day for skiing + tubing.
Clear - very light breeze from n.  Beautiful day.
Cloudless sky- NW wind- hard frost last night.
Warm south wind- very strong winds yesterday (25-35 mph).
Beautiful sunny- temp mid 60s- light SW wind.
Partly cloudy and very calm water.
Partly cloudy- calm- all trees except for pines and red maple defoliated by forest tent caterpillar.
Cloudy and light wind from the east.
Sunny- hot and a west wind.
Cloudy- southwest wind- and saw one loon chick this week.
Partly sunny- the temperature is in the 70s- north wind- and haven't seen the loon chick for a long time.
Very light wind and a nice warm day.
Partly cloudy and wind from the north.
Partly cloudy and a nice warm day.
Sunny and warm.  Last secchi reading for 2001.
First sample for 2002.  Late spring this year.  Partly cloudy.  Wind from SE.
SE wind.  Temp in 70s.  Nice day.  Loons on nest.
Sunny and cool.  Lots of rain this morning.
Mostly cloudy.  Humid.  First time in years that 2 chicks lived this long.
Partly cloudy.  South wind.  Temp 70s.  Loon chicks doing good.
Sunny- warm- light wind.  Lots of algae spots.
Partly cloudy- light wind.  Found loon nest today.
Little or no wind.  Sunny and warm.
Sunny and warm. Algae bloom - especially on west shore.
Light wind from NE. Sunny. Still lots of algae.
Little or no wind.  Warm. 80 F.
The water appears to have less tannins this year.  Light ESE wind.
Starting to see a bit of pollen on / in the water.
Lots of pollen.  Light SW wind.
Moderate wind from SW.  Just rained.
Not much rain this summer.  Lake level getting low.  Light SW wind.
Sunny and warm.  Light wind from north.
Sunny.  Light wind from SW.  Water is very low.
Overcast.  Dead calm.  Humid and hazy.
Sunny - no clouds at all.  1.4" rain last night.  Light wind.
Water is very low.  Partly cloudy.
Sunny- water is very clear and no tannins.
First time disk every hit bottom!  Clear and calm.  Water level is very low - water is very clear.  This lake used to have brown water full of tannins - now it's clear blue.
